l even know what you like to cook,
to eat, your favorite flowers.

00:45:31.426 --> 00:45:33.519
l know everything.

00:45:35.096 --> 00:45:37.724
l also know something else.

00:45:38.833 --> 00:45:43.668
You resent the fact
that Nikhil lends me money.

00:45:45.340 --> 00:45:47.774
So you really aren't a stranger to me.

00:45:48.276 --> 00:45:51.507
But l never imagined...

00:45:52.680 --> 00:45:57.140
l'd one day find myself
sitting by your side.

00:45:58.086 --> 00:46:01.487
-- Did you go to Rangpur?
-- Yes, l did.

00:46:01.589 --> 00:46:04.422
-- How was the trip?
-- Great.

00:46:04.859 --> 00:46:08.260
That's why the first thing l wanted
to see this morning was you.

00:46:09.664 --> 00:46:11.825
Don't you have to leave again?

00:46:11.933 --> 00:46:14.299
-- Where to?
-- To Rangpur.

00:46:14.402 --> 00:46:17.200
lsn't that your base?

00:46:17.905 --> 00:46:21.898
That was the idea, but not anymore.

00:46:22.443 --> 00:46:24.035
lt's not?

00:46:26.547 --> 00:46:28.481
Let me be frank with you.

00:46:29.016 --> 00:46:31.211
l want to be near you when l work.

00:46:35.790 --> 00:46:39.089
Just like a bee working for the queen.

00:46:39.193 --> 00:46:40.751
You'll be the queen bee.

00:46:43.898 --> 00:46:45.763
Do you have any objection?

00:46:47.101 --> 00:46:50.969
But won't you find it inconvenient
working from here?

00:46:57.078 --> 00:46:58.705
That's true.

00:47:01.549 --> 00:47:07.249
l don't think Nikhil will approve of this.

00:47:11.325 --> 00:47:13.020
But the thing is...

00:47:16.164 --> 00:47:18.394
l am essentially...

00:47:21.803 --> 00:47:23.634
a stubborn man.

00:47:25.473 --> 00:47:28.909
l just can't accept Nikhil's attitude.

00:47:31.679 --> 00:47:37.811
l want to promote
the Swadeshi cause right here...

00:47:39.020 --> 00:47:41.045
and l need your help.

00:47:42.790 --> 00:47:45.691
But l really know nothing about your work.

00:47:45.793 --> 00:47:49.524
l know that you
give speeches. ls that all?

00:47:51.933 --> 00:47:54.731
That's one of the most important things.

00:47:55.670 --> 00:47:58.036
Persuasion can work wonders.

00:47:59.807 --> 00:48:01.331
Wait.

00:48:02.643 --> 00:48:05.168
lf you really want to know about our work,

00:48:05.913 --> 00:48:07.380
then read this.

00:48:07.482 --> 00:48:08.744
OUR STRUGGLE

00:48:08.850 --> 00:48:11.444
lt contains everything you need to know.

00:48:16.257 --> 00:48:18.088
l will definitely read it.

00:48:20.027 --> 00:48:22.461
May l tell you something now?

00:48:23.664 --> 00:48:26.792
One of the biggest markets
in this area is here, in Sukhsayar.

00:48:26.901 --> 00:48:30.064
Did you know that?
-- So l've heard.

00:48:30.638 --> 00:48:36.440
lt's the only market in the area
where foreign goods are still being sold.

00:48:36.711 --> 00:48:40.545
Elsewhere, the landowners
have prohibited their sale,

00:48:40.648 --> 00:48:42.240
but Nikhil hasn't.

00:48:43.351 --> 00:48:45.945
l'm going to do my best to change that,

00:48:46.320 --> 00:48:51.053
but, with your help,
my task will be much easier.

00:48:51.158 --> 00:48:54.685
l'm afraid you're overestimating
my capabilities.

00:48:54.795 --> 00:48:56.660
Not at all.

00:48:57.465 --> 00:49:01.765
Nikhil may be my friend,
but he's your husband.

00:49:01.869 --> 00:49:04.838
You have much more influence
over him than l do.

00:49:04.939 --> 00:49:08.705
My husband isn't easily swayed.

00:49:09.010 --> 00:49:10.602
l know...

00:49:11.345 --> 00:49:14.178
but l think he'll listen to you.

00:49:18.886 --> 00:49:21.548
l know how much you mean to Nikhil.

00:49:22.924 --> 00:49:25.392
Will you try just once to persuade him?

00:49:27.995 --> 00:49:31.260
Nikhil's tenants wouldn't dare
to go against his will.

00:49:31.365 --> 00:49:34.596
He only has to tell them not to bring
any more foreign goods to the market.

00:49:35.770 --> 00:49:37.567
And if l fail to persuade him?

00:49:38.372 --> 00:49:41.068
l'll be happy if you just try.

00:49:42.343 --> 00:49:44.436
lf you fail, l'll find another way.

00:49:45.346 --> 00:49:47.337
Not without the queen bee's
knowledge, of course.

00:49:48.883 --> 00:49:51.477
Can l depend on you?

00:49:52.553 --> 00:49:54.111
l'll try my best.

00:50:01.963 --> 00:50:03.624
The more l see you,

00:50:04.332 --> 00:50:06.357
the more l admire you.

00:50:18.379 --> 00:50:19.778
l think l'll --

00:50:20.314 --> 00:50:22.612
Okay, you may go now.

00:50:26.821 --> 00:50:28.618
Oh, and one more thing.

00:50:30.591 --> 00:50:31.819
This item of yours.

00:50:39.500 --> 00:50:44.836
This is the only foreign item
l will keep with me.

00:50:49.610 --> 00:50:52.044
Did you see Sandip today?

00:50:53.280 --> 00:50:54.577
<i>Yes.</i>

00:50:57.284 --> 00:50:59.081
How is he doing?

00:51:00.554 --> 00:51:02.488
He's worried.

00:51:02.590 --> 00:51:04.080
Why?

00:51:05.760 --> 00:51:08.058
You won't let him promote
the Swadeshi cause here.

00:51:08.496 --> 00:51:11.897
Nonsense.
You heard me yourself.

00:51:12.266 --> 00:51:16.362
He's free to fight for his cause
as long as he leaves my estate alone.

00:51:17.872 --> 00:51:20.238
He says he's staying here.

00:51:21.542 --> 00:51:23.100
Staying here?

00:51:24.078 --> 00:51:25.568
That's what he says.

00:51:26.380 --> 00:51:28.541
He's going to stay and work here.

00:51:30.951 --> 00:51:32.976
That wouldn't be right.

00:51:34.221 --> 00:51:36.189
But all of Bengal has taken up
the Swadeshi cause.

00:51:36.290 --> 00:51:37.382
Why don't you?

00:51:38.426 --> 00:51:43.796
That would mean banning
all foreign goods from the market.

00:51:44.732 --> 00:51:47.530
Harish Kundu can do that, but not me.

00:51:48.369 --> 00:51:50.599
Surely the market belongs to you.
Why can't you?

00:51:51.605 --> 00:51:53.596
lt's not my market, Bimala.

00:51:54.108 --> 00:51:57.373
The market belongs to the traders
who sell their goods there.

00:51:57.478 --> 00:51:59.139
They're poor.

00:52:00.748 --> 00:52:05.617
Foreign goods are cheaper
and of better quality than lndian goods.

00:52:07.688 --> 00:52:11.715
The poor villagers can afford them.
How can l force them not to buy them?

00:52:14.695 --> 00:52:18.859
Swadeshi is for those who can afford it,

00:52:18.966 --> 00:52:20.797
not for the poor.

00:52:25.773 --> 00:52:27.502
What are you thinking?

00:52:28.375 --> 00:52:30.275
Can we follow Swadeshi...

00:52:32.780 --> 00:52:34.509
without making the poor suffer?

00:52:34.615 --> 00:52:36.310
ls it possible?

00:52:36.984 --> 00:52:40.420
lf it were possible,
l'd definitely support Swadeshi.

00:52:41.555 --> 00:52:43.989
You believe the very idea
of Swadeshi is wrong.

00:52:45.392 --> 00:52:48.054
Even if l do,
who would listen to me?

00:52:48.162 --> 00:52:50.596
The entire country supports Swadeshi.

00:52:51.398 --> 00:52:53.889
You yourself believe Sandip is right.

00:52:54.001 --> 00:52:56.231
Many others must feel the same way.

00:52:58.139 --> 00:53:04.977
But l believe that coercing the poor
can only harm our country.

00:53:10.851 --> 00:53:13.251
l can see you're not convinced.

00:53:14.355 --> 00:53:16.983
l was looking at it differently.

00:53:17.091 --> 00:53:20.686
l was thinking that
something has to be done.

00:53:20.795 --> 00:53:22.820
Even if it means
hardship for the poor now,

00:53:22.930 --> 00:53:25.125
it will help them in the long run.

00:53:25.533 --> 00:53:28.502
The Swadeshi care about this country.

00:53:30.070 --> 00:53:36.373
l believe what they care about
is an abstract idea of this country,

00:53:36.477 --> 00:53:39.071
this country as the Mother Goddess.

00:53:39.880 --> 00:53:41.677
The nation is our mother.

00:53:41.782 --> 00:53:47.015
Worship our mother,
work for our mother, pray to our mother.

00:53:47.788 --> 00:53:50.621
Everything you do is for our mother.

00:53:51.292 --> 00:53:53.726
Heal our mother's pain.

00:53:54.461 --> 00:53:56.122
l can understand that.

00:53:56.964 --> 00:53:59.762
And l can understand why
that idea appeals to women.

00:54:00.401 --> 00:54:03.234
l know how you feel, Bimala,

00:54:03.337 --> 00:54:05.703
but l don't feel the same way.

00:54:29.763 --> 00:54:31.924
Those things you said tonight...

00:54:32.266 --> 00:54:34.427
Were those your own thoughts?

00:54:34.535 --> 00:54:36.696
Why are you asking me this?

00:54:38.873 --> 00:54:41.899
l felt as if you were speaking for Sandip.

00:54:42.009 --> 00:54:44.910
Sandip is your friend, not mine.

00:54:46.513 --> 00:54:51.712
l thought you two had teamed up
''in right earnest'' to fight for a higher cause.

00:54:52.620 --> 00:54:55.987
He's working on the public front,
and you on the domestic.

00:54:56.090 --> 00:54:57.648
What an idea!

00:55:05.900 --> 00:55:08.061
Will you have daily meetings?

00:55:08.602 --> 00:55:13.471
You insisted that l meet your friend,
so you can spare me the insinuations.

00:55:26.921 --> 00:55:29.549
l just asked a simple question.

00:55:30.324 --> 00:55:32.884
l wasn't insinuating anything.
-- Very well.

00:55:32.993 --> 00:55:36.019
lf it upsets you so much,
l won't go outside anymore.

00:55:36.931 --> 00:55:38.865
You're mistaken, Bimala.

00:55:38.966 --> 00:55:41.230
l'm not upset at all.

00:55:41.735 --> 00:55:44.898
After all, l know you both so well.

00:55:45.005 --> 00:55:49.465
Why shouldn't you go outside?
-- Because l don't want to.

00:55:50.577 --> 00:55:52.169
You're being unreasonable.

00:55:52.279 --> 00:55:55.840
l've been out twice already.
l don't have to go out every day.

00:55:58.585 --> 00:56:00.314
Very well.

00:56:10.331 --> 00:56:15.598
l won't restrict you
from going where you please.

00:56:16.870 --> 00:56:21.671
As l told you,
you are completely free.

00:56:22.810 --> 00:56:27.247
But l must tell you one thing.

00:56:29.116 --> 00:56:33.143
lf you tell me you want to give up
wearing foreign clothes,

00:56:33.754 --> 00:56:38.748
or do without your foreign
perfumes, shoes and soap,

00:56:39.059 --> 00:56:41.289
l won't mind at all.

00:56:41.595 --> 00:56:43.995
But clamping down on poor traders

00:56:45.666 --> 00:56:48.794
by banning foreign goods in the market

00:56:49.737 --> 00:56:52.797
means going against
my own beliefs and principles.

00:56:53.374 --> 00:56:55.672
l could never do that, Bimala.

00:57:02.116 --> 00:57:06.052
Swadeshi is something l can't take lightly.

00:57:12.326 --> 00:57:16.820
<i>The weak say, ''Whatever fate</i>
<i>has given to me is mine. "</i>

00:57:16.930 --> 00:57:21.264
<i>And the impotent agree with them.</i>

00:57:21.368 --> 00:57:24.132
<i>''OnIy what I can snatch away</i>
<i>by force is mine. "</i>

00:57:24.238 --> 00:57:26.763
<i>That is what experience has taught us.</i>

00:57:26.874 --> 00:57:30.037
<i>My country is not mine</i>
<i>simpIy because I was born here.</i>

00:57:30.144 --> 00:57:34.012
<i>It becomes mine</i>
<i>onIy when I am abIe to win it by force.</i>

00:57:34.114 --> 00:57:36.446
<i>OnIy then can the nation be mine.</i>

00:57:41.889 --> 00:57:48.954
This funeral pyre celebrates the cremation
of foreign trade in your village.

00:57:49.763 --> 00:57:52.027
These ashes are sacred.

00:57:52.399 --> 00:57:54.128
Hail Motherland!

00:58:09.616 --> 00:58:14.918
AN URGENT MATTER
REGARDlNG OUR CAUSE

00:58:26.166 --> 00:58:30.068
-- Please give this to Mrs. Choudhury.
-- Very well.

00:59:11.845 --> 00:59:13.904
Madam isn't feeling well, sir.

00:59:18.919 --> 00:59:20.750
l see.

00:59:31.798 --> 00:59:34.926
-- You know the headmaster, don't you?
-- Yes, of course.

00:59:35.035 --> 00:59:38.266
Good morning.
l hope you are doing well.

00:59:39.473 --> 00:59:42.237
Not as long as you're around.

00:59:45.879 --> 00:59:47.176
How come?

00:59:47.581 --> 00:59:51.017
His students have all disappeared
since you arrived.

00:59:52.553 --> 00:59:58.082
But you must admit that working
for one's country helps build character.

01:00:00.794 --> 01:00:05.197
One of my students was influenced
by the Swadeshi movement.

01:00:05.299 --> 01:00:09.201
He threw a stone at Mrs. Choudhury's
governess, Miss Gilby.

01:00:09.803 --> 01:00:12.567
Would you consider that
an example of character building?

01:00:13.106 --> 01:00:16.371
But that happened before l came.

01:00:16.910 --> 01:00:19.208
You can't blame me for that.

01:00:19.313 --> 01:00:22.680
After all, you must admit
that a few such incidents

01:00:22.783 --> 01:00:27.186
are inevitable in times
of great social upheaval.

01:00:27.754 --> 01:00:30.382
You even roped in my best student.

01:00:30.490 --> 01:00:32.583
Who? Amulya?

01:00:34.361 --> 01:00:36.625
He'd have won a scholarship
if he'd taken his exam.

01:00:36.730 --> 01:00:39.460
You stole that opportunity from him.

01:00:40.000 --> 01:00:43.163
Amulya? l didn't rope him in.
He joined of his own accord.

01:00:43.670 --> 01:00:48.334
What about the other rowdy dissolutes
who have joined your team?

01:00:48.442 --> 01:00:51.536
They're the worst troublemakers in the village.

01:00:51.645 --> 01:00:54.170
They're not troublemakers anymore, sir.

01:00:54.281 --> 01:00:57.182
They're fighting for the cause.
They're working hard.

01:00:57.651 --> 01:01:01.519
With two exceptions,
everyone here is working for the cause.

01:01:01.622 --> 01:01:03.283
One of them is you.

01:01:04.157 --> 01:01:08.093
The other one is your former
student Nikhilesh Choudhury.

01:01:08.195 --> 01:01:11.426
l regret that
l couldn't persuade him to join.

01:01:11.531 --> 01:01:14.295
Like you, he turns a deaf ear
to the Swadeshi cause.

01:01:14.401 --> 01:01:17.336
No, he isn't against Swadeshi ideals.

01:01:17.437 --> 01:01:21.567
He's against your
destructive brand of Swadeshi.

01:01:22.175 --> 01:01:24.439
He practiced Swadeshi long before you,

01:01:24.544 --> 01:01:27.513
and he never relied
on any battle cries or mantras.

01:01:27.614 --> 01:01:30.378
-- l know that.
-- You know nothing!

01:01:30.484 --> 01:01:32.577
Do you know about his Swadeshi bank?

01:01:32.686 --> 01:01:36.144
Or his Swadeshi sugar factory,
his soap factory?

01:01:36.256 --> 01:01:41.489
Do you know he set up his own looms
for weaving Swadeshi cloth?

01:01:41.895 --> 01:01:46.798
Where were you
and your ''Hail Motherland'' then?

01:01:47.334 --> 01:01:50.861
Do you know how much
he spent for Swadeshi?

01:01:50.971 --> 01:01:52.996
-- Please, headmaster --
-- You stay out of this!

01:01:53.106 --> 01:01:57.509
These things must be said.
-- But that's what l keep telling him.

01:01:57.611 --> 01:02:01.240
lf both of us have the same goals,
then why doesn't he join us?

01:02:01.348 --> 01:02:05.250
You don't have the same goals.
There are many differences.

01:02:05.352 --> 01:02:09.721
Your goal is power and leadership.

01:02:09.823 --> 01:02:11.984
You don't care about the people!

01:02:12.092 --> 01:02:14.890
Nikhil never thought about himself.

01:02:14.995 --> 01:02:19.728
People are applauding you
and singing your praises.

01:02:20.600 --> 01:02:22.932
Nikhil was ridiculed.

01:02:23.036 --> 01:02:27.666
He had no head for business,
so his brand of Swadeshi didn't last.

01:02:27.774 --> 01:02:30.106
But his way was the right way.

01:02:30.544 --> 01:02:32.136
Yours is wrong.

01:02:32.245 --> 01:02:33.872
lt's more than wrong.

01:02:33.980 --> 01:02:36.039
lt's dangerous.

01:02:38.652 --> 01:02:40.347
Give those to me.

01:02:41.521 --> 01:02:44.354
l'll drop by this evening.

01:02:48.562 --> 01:02:50.462
My goodness.

01:02:53.600 --> 01:02:57.001
Please, Nikhil, l implore you.

01:02:57.104 --> 01:02:59.902
Keep that headmaster away from me.

01:03:00.006 --> 01:03:03.965
l came here to give speeches,
not listen to them.

01:03:05.645 --> 01:03:07.636
Are you planning to stay here and work?

01:03:14.888 --> 01:03:19.382
l'm going to speak
at your market this afternoon.

01:03:20.894 --> 01:03:23.192
That's where our greatest
challenge lies, Nikhil.

01:03:24.664 --> 01:03:29.727
Not where the landowner
is already in favor of Swadeshi,

01:03:31.405 --> 01:03:33.202
but where he isn't.

01:03:33.306 --> 01:03:35.331
But remember, Sandip,

01:03:35.942 --> 01:03:38.740
most of my tenants are poor Muslims.

01:03:40.380 --> 01:03:45.408
l don't want them harassed.

01:03:46.920 --> 01:03:51.584
lf l see that happening,
l will be forced to intervene.

01:03:52.959 --> 01:03:56.053
lf they prove to be obstacles
to our revolution,

01:03:56.329 --> 01:03:58.729
l'll have to take the necessary measures.

01:03:59.199 --> 01:04:01.099
Many Muslims have accepted Swadeshi.

01:04:02.335 --> 01:04:04.200
They were forced to do so.

01:04:05.605 --> 01:04:07.573
lt will happen here too.

01:04:11.044 --> 01:04:12.944
l've said what l had to say.

01:04:13.780 --> 01:04:18.046
What you do now is up to you.

01:04:24.257 --> 01:04:26.487
As you all know,

01:04:26.593 --> 01:04:28.925
our English rulers

01:04:29.029 --> 01:04:32.965
have divided Bengal in two.

01:04:33.400 --> 01:04:40.932
This amounts to erecting a wall
between Hindus and Muslims.

01:04:41.274 --> 01:04:46.769
They have not given us
the right to break this wall,

01:04:46.880 --> 01:04:51.283
but, to foil the government,
we have chosen a different path.

01:04:51.384 --> 01:04:54.012
One important way to fight the partition

01:04:54.120 --> 01:04:59.353
is to stop selling foreign goods
in our markets.

01:05:00.060 --> 01:05:05.760
Salt, sugar, cloth and soap
are all everyday items

01:05:05.866 --> 01:05:09.165
which are only available
as foreign products at your market.

01:05:09.870 --> 01:05:12.304
By selling their foreign goods here,

01:05:12.405 --> 01:05:17.536
the British are making
a lot of money in our country,

01:05:17.644 --> 01:05:22.479
while we keep growing poorer.

01:05:22.582 --> 01:05:25.176
This is wrong.
This must stop.

01:05:25.285 --> 01:05:28.743
We've tolerated this up to now,
but no more.

01:05:29.356 --> 01:05:35.454
l know that lndian substitutes
for foreign goods are not always available,

01:05:35.562 --> 01:05:40.295
so you've had to trade with foreign goods
because that's all you had.

01:05:40.400 --> 01:05:43.767
But if we can all make sacrifices

01:05:43.870 --> 01:05:47.772
and produce our own goods,

01:05:47.874 --> 01:05:51.605
then we will overcome these difficulties.

01:05:51.878 --> 01:05:55.211
Brothers, we are depending on you.

01:05:55.815 --> 01:05:57.749
lf you come forward and join us,

01:05:57.851 --> 01:06:00.718
together we will stop
the partitioning of Bengal

01:06:00.820 --> 01:06:03.288
and regain our pride.

01:06:03.823 --> 01:06:08.283
And now, do you see
this circle here before me?

01:06:08.395 --> 01:06:13.662
Throw all your foreign goods
into the circle of flags.

01:06:14.534 --> 01:06:17.594
lndian substitutes will be made.

01:06:18.438 --> 01:06:21.498
Many manufacturers
have come forward to help us.

01:06:21.942 --> 01:06:25.105
Have no fear of losing your livelihood.

01:06:25.745 --> 01:06:29.408
Today's loss will not be lost forever.

01:06:29.516 --> 01:06:34.283
Now l ask you to throw all
of your foreign goods into the circle.

01:06:34.654 --> 01:06:39.648
The land that gave birth to you,
the land that you love...

01:06:39.759 --> 01:06:42.250
Now is the time to help her.

01:06:42.729 --> 01:06:46.426
Foreign cloth, foreign thread,

01:06:46.533 --> 01:06:49.764
foreign sugar, foreign salt,

01:06:50.337 --> 01:06:52.134
foreign scissors and knives,

01:06:52.238 --> 01:06:55.730
foreign matches,
and everything else foreign...

01:06:55.842 --> 01:06:58.367
Throw them in that circle.

01:06:58.478 --> 01:07:02.107
We beseech you.
Don't just sit there.

01:07:02.215 --> 01:07:04.547
Help the Swadeshi cause.

01:07:04.651 --> 01:07:08.610
We want to hear it from the maharaja!
Let him come here.

01:07:09.122 --> 01:07:10.487
We won't listen to you!

01:07:12.392 --> 01:07:14.917
Your maharaja is my friend.

01:07:15.028 --> 01:07:17.428
l'm his guest.

01:07:17.530 --> 01:07:20.795
lsn't that proof enough
that l have his support?

01:07:20.900 --> 01:07:23.892
We're traders.
lf we have nothing to sell, we'll starve!

01:07:24.004 --> 01:07:27.098
We've tried selling lndian goods.

01:07:27.207 --> 01:07:28.504
Nobody buys them.

01:07:28.608 --> 01:07:31.406
You're a gentleman.
You have money.

01:07:31.511 --> 01:07:35.242
lt's easy for you to say,
''Don't sell foreign goods.''

01:07:35.348 --> 01:07:38.181
We're poor!
How will we survive?

01:07:44.457 --> 01:07:47.426
<i>It's cIear that persuasion</i>
<i>won't work on NikhiI's estate.</i>

01:07:47.527 --> 01:07:50.121
<i>We'II have to use other means.</i>

01:07:50.597 --> 01:07:55.261
<i>Any compromise on foreign goods</i>
<i>wouId crippIe our movement.</i>

01:07:57.337 --> 01:08:00.397
<i>HaiI MotherIand!</i>

01:08:39.312 --> 01:08:40.779
This is Mr. Kulada.

01:08:40.880 --> 01:08:42.575
Greetings.

01:08:42.682 --> 01:08:43.774
Please follow me.

01:08:49.456 --> 01:08:52.391
Were those stolen from the villagers?

01:08:59.232 --> 01:09:00.699
Have a seat.

01:09:01.501 --> 01:09:06.063
You may enjoy your bonfire, but the villagers
will file a complaint against you.

01:09:08.341 --> 01:09:11.777
We'll set fire to their crops if they do.

01:09:13.046 --> 01:09:14.638
Can't we try picketing?

01:09:16.583 --> 01:09:18.175
We can make them understand.

01:09:18.685 --> 01:09:20.676
lt's worked in other places.

01:09:21.221 --> 01:09:23.382
l know what works and what doesn't.

01:09:23.490 --> 01:09:25.685
Picketing won't work in Sukhsayar.

01:09:27.627 --> 01:09:29.458
Please sit, Mr. Kulada.

01:09:36.336 --> 01:09:38.497
A foreign brand, l see.

01:09:38.605 --> 01:09:41.472
Yes, it's the only exception
l make to Swadeshi.

01:09:41.574 --> 01:09:44.236
-- May l have one?
-- Be my guest.

01:09:47.447 --> 01:09:49.142
These people can't be persuaded, Amulya.

01:09:49.582 --> 01:09:51.413
They've been pampered too much.

01:09:51.518 --> 01:09:58.890
Listen, l've been the manager of this estate
since the maharaja's father was alive.

01:10:00.593 --> 01:10:03.084
The father was a tough one.

01:10:03.196 --> 01:10:05.426
The trouble is the son.

01:10:05.532 --> 01:10:07.557
lf only he'd been firm with them,

01:10:07.667 --> 01:10:11.398
he could have brought
these villagers to their knees.

01:10:11.504 --> 01:10:14.337
lt would have been smooth sailing for you.

01:10:16.843 --> 01:10:19.903
Anyway, tell me how you can help us.

01:10:21.281 --> 01:10:25.240
lf you can't stop the influx
of foreign goods,

01:10:26.052 --> 01:10:29.488
you can't stop the trade of foreign goods.

01:10:30.590 --> 01:10:34.617
Those boats bring the goods in.

01:10:35.662 --> 01:10:39.928
-- You'll have to deal with the boatmen first.
-- Can you do that for me?

01:10:41.134 --> 01:10:46.868
The problem is that the boatmen's
leader is very stubborn.

01:10:48.541 --> 01:10:50.532
Who is he?
What's his name?

01:10:50.643 --> 01:10:54.340
Mirjan.
He's a hard nut to crack.

01:10:55.815 --> 01:10:59.512
-- Can he be persuaded?
-- Where there's a will, there's a way.

01:11:00.420 --> 01:11:06.120
A boat which sails
is also a boat which sinks.

01:11:09.662 --> 01:11:13.689
But it's going to take
more than words to do this job.

01:11:14.534 --> 01:11:17.230
lt will take...
-- Money?

01:11:17.837 --> 01:11:20.271
We have to stop tongues from wagging,

01:11:20.373 --> 01:11:23.934
pay compensation,
bribe the police.

01:11:24.043 --> 01:11:25.806
That all takes money.

01:11:29.115 --> 01:11:31.606
lt's not like we don't have any money,

01:11:31.718 --> 01:11:35.176
and more can be raised if necessary.

01:11:35.288 --> 01:11:38.382
Then you can rely on me.

01:11:39.192 --> 01:11:43.219
l'll do the dirty work,

01:11:43.329 --> 01:11:46.856
but if something goes wrong,

01:11:46.966 --> 01:11:48.763
you're on your own.

01:11:51.571 --> 01:11:54.096
You don't need to worry about that.

01:11:54.207 --> 01:11:56.937
Even so, if l get into any sort of trouble,

01:11:57.043 --> 01:11:59.739
l have no intention of taking all the blame.

01:12:07.854 --> 01:12:10.516
l'm keeping this letter you wrote me.

01:12:13.726 --> 01:12:15.785
<i>I didn't go.</i>

01:12:15.895 --> 01:12:17.829
<i>He asked for me.</i>

01:12:17.931 --> 01:12:23.096
<i>I gave an excuse and stayed inside,</i>
<i>but what good did it do?</i>

01:12:23.202 --> 01:12:27.161
<i>I was thinking of him aII day yesterday.</i>

01:12:27.273 --> 01:12:30.003
<i>Why shouId this happen to a woman</i>

01:12:30.109 --> 01:12:36.605
<i>who has never thought about any man</i>
<i>other than her own husband?</i>

01:12:37.050 --> 01:12:39.848
Madam, how do you want
the fish prepared?

01:12:39.953 --> 01:12:41.818
You never told me.

01:12:42.789 --> 01:12:44.984
Make a curry with ground mustard seed.

01:12:53.866 --> 01:12:54.992
<i>Madam?</i>

01:12:56.970 --> 01:12:58.562
Yes, Nanku?

01:12:58.671 --> 01:13:00.866
<i>There's a Ietter for you.</i>

01:13:05.878 --> 01:13:08.870
OUR STRUGGLE

01:13:10.116 --> 01:13:12.050
Are you feeling any better?

01:13:13.987 --> 01:13:14.851
Yes.

01:13:15.621 --> 01:13:19.148
This boy from our group
was very eager to meet you.

01:13:22.829 --> 01:13:25.764
You met me once before when l was little.

01:13:25.865 --> 01:13:27.560
l came with my mother.

01:13:27.667 --> 01:13:30.192
-- What's your mother's name?
-- Soudamini Devi.

01:13:32.005 --> 01:13:35.941
-- Are you Nibaron Ghosal's son?
-- Yes. My name is Amulya.

01:13:37.810 --> 01:13:40.677
-- How old are you?
-- Seventeen.

01:13:40.780 --> 01:13:43.248
l was about to take
my final exam, but l didn't.

01:13:43.850 --> 01:13:45.943
Because of Swadeshi?

01:13:46.052 --> 01:13:47.952
Amulya is very hardworking.

01:13:48.921 --> 01:13:50.889
He remembers the entire <i>Bhagavadgita.</i>

01:13:51.724 --> 01:13:53.521
Really?

01:13:54.427 --> 01:13:55.894
Here it is.

01:13:55.995 --> 01:13:58.896
-- Do you always carry it with you?
-- Always.

01:13:58.998 --> 01:14:02.525
The <i>Bhagavadgita</i> gives one courage
to overcome one's fears.

01:14:02.635 --> 01:14:04.762
Even to die for one's country.

01:14:07.440 --> 01:14:09.908
Aren't you afraid to die?

01:14:10.009 --> 01:14:12.876
''For the soul, there is neither birth
nor death at any time.

01:14:12.979 --> 01:14:16.244
He has not come into being, does not come
into being, and will not come into being.

01:14:16.349 --> 01:14:19.443
He is unborn, eternal,
ever--existing and primeval.

01:14:19.552 --> 01:14:22.578
He is not slain when the body is slain.''

01:14:22.688 --> 01:14:25.020
Even when a man dies,
his soul lives on.

01:14:25.124 --> 01:14:27.592
Okay, Amulya.
You may go now.

01:14:29.662 --> 01:14:32.096
Mr. Sandip said you believe in Swadeshi.

01:14:32.198 --> 01:14:34.564
l wanted to pay my respects.

01:14:34.667 --> 01:14:35.964
l'll take my leave, sister.

01:14:36.936 --> 01:14:39.427
l'll come again.
-- Please do.

01:14:39.539 --> 01:14:40.836
Hail Motherland.

01:14:42.208 --> 01:14:44.438
-- Hail Motherland.
-- Good--bye.

01:14:55.888 --> 01:14:57.583
What are you thinking?

01:14:58.458 --> 01:15:02.258
ls there any danger to your life
in the work you do?

01:15:05.198 --> 01:15:06.688
Well...

01:15:08.501 --> 01:15:12.767
Since we're fighting against
the powerful British government,

01:15:14.707 --> 01:15:16.265
of course there is.

01:15:23.082 --> 01:15:26.108
But my boys are brave.

01:15:27.753 --> 01:15:29.516
My courage doesn't begin to match theirs.

01:15:29.622 --> 01:15:32.216
That's a strange confession from a leader.

01:15:35.495 --> 01:15:37.861
Sometimes the truth comes out.

01:15:42.902 --> 01:15:44.836
Now will you tell me the truth?

01:15:46.405 --> 01:15:47.667
What truth?

01:15:49.008 --> 01:15:51.272
After so many years,

01:15:51.377 --> 01:15:54.107
why did you suddenly decide
to come out of your confinement?

01:15:54.814 --> 01:15:57.044
Don't you know why?

01:15:57.450 --> 01:15:59.315
How would l know?

01:15:59.418 --> 01:16:01.386
You should know.

01:16:02.555 --> 01:16:06.457
You should, but you're a man.

01:16:06.559 --> 01:16:08.550
You don't have a woman's intuition.

01:16:10.496 --> 01:16:11.724
Will you tell me?

01:16:28.714 --> 01:16:29.908
Why?

01:16:39.125 --> 01:16:42.583
l'd never been face--to--face
with a leader before.

01:16:44.730 --> 01:16:48.632
l fear the leader may have let you down.

01:16:56.709 --> 01:16:59.371
Not so far.

01:17:23.269 --> 01:17:24.827
You play the piano too?

01:17:26.405 --> 01:17:28.396
l was taking lessons.

01:17:28.741 --> 01:17:30.106
Piano...

01:17:31.143 --> 01:17:32.735
singing.

01:17:33.646 --> 01:17:35.409
English songs?

01:18:07.747 --> 01:18:09.544
You didn't come yesterday.

01:18:10.149 --> 01:18:15.086
l had a feeling you weren't really ill.

01:18:15.855 --> 01:18:18.585
l racked my brain all day trying to guess...

01:18:19.625 --> 01:18:26.224
what l had done or said to annoy you.

01:18:28.701 --> 01:18:32.193
You still haven't told me
why you called.

01:18:32.838 --> 01:18:35.102
l just wanted to see you.

01:18:36.676 --> 01:18:38.405
ls that the only reason?

01:18:41.480 --> 01:18:43.573
l didn't see you yesterday,

01:18:44.150 --> 01:18:46.277
and it turned out
to be a dismal day for me.

01:18:46.819 --> 01:18:49.151
My pride as a leader...

01:18:50.122 --> 01:18:51.714
was badly shaken.

01:18:52.692 --> 01:18:54.785
The people won't listen to you?

01:18:55.261 --> 01:18:58.594
Sometimes words are not enough.

01:18:58.698 --> 01:19:02.691
-- What do you do then?
-- l try other ways.

01:19:03.369 --> 01:19:04.836
May l know what ways?

01:19:06.405 --> 01:19:08.896
Because my husband's
not going to help you.

01:19:13.312 --> 01:19:14.506
Nikhil said so?

01:19:23.289 --> 01:19:25.553
Do you know what l feel
like doing sometimes?

01:19:26.392 --> 01:19:28.292
To hell with Swadeshi.

01:19:28.861 --> 01:19:31.694
l'll spend my life
chatting with the queen bee.

01:19:33.599 --> 01:19:35.157
With me?

01:19:35.634 --> 01:19:36.601
Chatting?

01:19:37.837 --> 01:19:39.600
Would that bother you?

01:19:43.042 --> 01:19:44.509
Why are you laughing?

01:19:45.077 --> 01:19:47.773
That's so absurd.

01:19:47.880 --> 01:19:51.941
You're not the type to spend
even an hour chatting.

01:19:55.087 --> 01:19:56.554
You're right.

01:19:58.190 --> 01:19:59.589
The truth is...

01:20:00.860 --> 01:20:02.555
l need Swadeshi...

01:20:04.130 --> 01:20:06.030
just as much as l need you.

01:20:08.734 --> 01:20:11.794
l don't want you to stop
fighting for the country.

01:20:12.972 --> 01:20:17.272
My husband and l don't see
eye to eye on that matter.

01:20:17.743 --> 01:20:22.305
He has many virtues,
and l admire him for that.

01:20:22.982 --> 01:20:29.114
But, for a man, he is much too placid.

01:20:29.221 --> 01:20:32.657
A person can't afford to be so placid
at a time like this.

01:20:36.195 --> 01:20:38.891
l agree with you entirely.

01:20:40.566 --> 01:20:44.696
My husband says
you don't care about the poor,

01:20:44.804 --> 01:20:48.171
so you can't really do
any good for our country.

01:20:50.976 --> 01:20:54.742
l don't believe you would hurt the poor.

01:20:55.247 --> 01:20:58.546
You'll try to persuade them.
That's all.

01:21:05.024 --> 01:21:06.958
But the problem is...

01:21:09.395 --> 01:21:11.829
persuasion doesn't always work.

01:21:13.866 --> 01:21:17.358
You need something more.
-- What do you need?

01:21:20.973 --> 01:21:24.136
-- Let's not talk about that.
-- l want to know.

01:21:25.511 --> 01:21:28.036
l don't want to talk
about mundane things with you.

01:21:28.147 --> 01:21:29.546
Why?

01:21:31.984 --> 01:21:35.181
l want no note of discord
in our relationship.

01:21:36.155 --> 01:21:38.715
But l'd be really happy to help.

01:21:40.426 --> 01:21:41.723
This is beyond you, queen bee.

01:21:42.828 --> 01:21:45.023
Haven't you seen me going beyond?

01:21:46.165 --> 01:21:50.625
l know how far you can go.
Even so, l'd rather not talk about it.

01:21:50.736 --> 01:21:52.465
lt's a personal request.

01:21:53.572 --> 01:21:58.771
Then there's no reason for me to stay.

01:21:59.545 --> 01:22:01.012
l'm leaving.

01:22:01.113 --> 01:22:05.015
Queen bee, please don't leave angry!

01:22:05.117 --> 01:22:09.611
lf l can't help you with Swadeshi,
then l'm just wasting my time here.

01:22:09.722 --> 01:22:12.190
l just didn't want you to worry about me.

01:22:12.825 --> 01:22:15.521
Must we only talk about politics?

01:22:15.628 --> 01:22:17.095
Only about my work?

01:22:17.696 --> 01:22:21.154
Promise me you'll tell me
if you need money,

01:22:21.267 --> 01:22:24.236
and you'll take it if l give it to you.

01:22:24.870 --> 01:22:26.394
l promise, queen bee.

01:22:27.039 --> 01:22:28.802
l promise.

01:22:29.074 --> 01:22:30.541
Queen bee?

01:22:31.210 --> 01:22:34.077
l'll come again this evening.
Please wait for me here.

01:22:34.547 --> 01:22:37.038
l hate having to send for you every time.

01:22:37.583 --> 01:22:39.175
Let go of me.

01:22:39.285 --> 01:22:43.346
Promise me you'll come to me every day.

01:22:44.323 --> 01:22:47.121
l must see you at least once a day.

01:22:48.394 --> 01:22:50.726
There's nothing wrong with that.

01:22:51.030 --> 01:22:53.362
Promise me.

01:22:53.465 --> 01:22:55.160
All right.

01:22:56.969 --> 01:23:01.065
Please let go of my hand.
l want to go.

01:23:24.863 --> 01:23:27.331
Khemi, clean the room later.

01:24:42.941 --> 01:24:48.573
<i>GentIy she waIks,</i>
<i>the beauteous one</i>

01:24:55.154 --> 01:24:57.213
Back so soon?

01:25:01.460 --> 01:25:03.223
What are you staring at?

01:25:05.431 --> 01:25:07.524
What is there to stare at but you?

01:25:08.634 --> 01:25:10.829
l've never seen anything like it.

01:25:12.104 --> 01:25:14.038
Such tender concern for our guest.

01:25:14.473 --> 01:25:16.839
He'll never want to leave.

01:25:18.577 --> 01:25:23.071
ln my day, we had to look
after our husbands too.

01:25:25.517 --> 01:25:29.578
lf only my brother--in--law
were a guest in his own house,

01:25:30.289 --> 01:25:32.120
he'd be warmly welcomed.

01:25:32.224 --> 01:25:35.193
l don't want any advice from you.

01:25:40.632 --> 01:25:43.795
l was just a small girl
when l came here as a bride.

01:25:44.570 --> 01:25:49.132
Your husband was
my playmate in those days.

01:25:51.043 --> 01:25:52.738
Where were you then?

01:25:52.845 --> 01:25:55.973
There's no need to repeat
what l already know.

01:26:00.986 --> 01:26:03.454
He was the only one
who understood my pain.

01:26:03.555 --> 01:26:05.113
He used to say,

01:26:05.824 --> 01:26:08.486
''We're still living in the Dark Ages.

01:26:09.161 --> 01:26:11.254
That's why you're suffering like this.

01:26:12.931 --> 01:26:16.958
For you, having a husband
is just as painful as losing one.''

01:26:17.469 --> 01:26:22.532
''My wife will be a free woman,'' he'd say.

01:26:25.744 --> 01:26:28.713
Well, now l see that free woman
before my very eyes.

01:26:32.985 --> 01:26:35.146
But don't forget,

01:26:36.155 --> 01:26:38.180
there's a God above us, dear sister.

01:26:38.724 --> 01:26:42.182
He can see you too.

01:26:55.507 --> 01:26:57.941
<i>I beIieved I had the strength to bear</i>

01:26:58.610 --> 01:27:03.707
<i>whatever misfortune</i>
<i>fate had in store for me.</i>

01:27:04.183 --> 01:27:09.712
<i>I wouId caII up visions of suffering</i>
<i>and steeI myseIf against them.</i>

01:27:10.489 --> 01:27:12.457
<i>Visions of poverty,</i>

01:27:12.558 --> 01:27:16.392
<i>dishonor or death.</i>

01:27:17.095 --> 01:27:20.622
<i>I even imagined BimaIa's death.</i>

01:27:21.800 --> 01:27:25.258
<i>But there was one thing</i>
<i>I couId never imagine happening.</i>

01:27:26.438 --> 01:27:30.397
<i>Now I keep asking myseIf</i>
<i>again and again.</i>

01:27:31.376 --> 01:27:33.537
<i>Do I have the strength to bear this?</i>

01:27:34.813 --> 01:27:39.079
-- Hail Motherland!
-- Hail Motherland!

01:27:59.171 --> 01:28:03.699
-- What do you want?
-- We have some questions.

01:28:03.809 --> 01:28:04.969
What are they?

01:28:05.077 --> 01:28:08.308
Why don't you ban
foreign goods in our market?

01:28:08.413 --> 01:28:11.576
-- l have my reasons.
-- ls it because you would lose money?

01:28:13.952 --> 01:28:18.184
l wouldn't, but the poor would.

01:28:18.557 --> 01:28:20.286
But our nation will profit.

01:28:20.392 --> 01:28:24.385
We buy domestic salt, sugar and clothing.

01:28:24.496 --> 01:28:26.191
How can you say that?

01:28:26.999 --> 01:28:29.627
How can you compare
yourselves with the poor?

01:28:30.102 --> 01:28:32.036
You have money.

01:28:32.137 --> 01:28:35.129
You can afford
to spend more on lndian goods.

01:28:36.675 --> 01:28:39.143
The poor aren't standing in your way.

01:28:39.811 --> 01:28:41.176
Why are you standing in theirs?

01:28:41.580 --> 01:28:44.549
You want to oppose an entire nation
that's taken the Swadeshi oath?

01:28:44.650 --> 01:28:45.446
Never.

01:28:46.485 --> 01:28:48.385
That's beyond my power.

01:28:49.087 --> 01:28:52.318
But how can you say
the entire nation has taken your oath?

01:28:53.125 --> 01:28:54.888
Look at the evidence.

01:28:54.993 --> 01:28:57.393
Aren't the traders part of this nation?

01:28:57.496 --> 01:29:00.761
So you won't ban foreign goods?

01:29:02.367 --> 01:29:03.766
No,

01:29:04.269 --> 01:29:07.102
because those goods don't belong to me.

01:29:07.205 --> 01:29:08.900
Hail Motherland!

01:29:30.796 --> 01:29:32.195
What are you looking for?

01:29:33.565 --> 01:29:35.294
<i>PassifIora.</i>

01:29:36.668 --> 01:29:38.602
Didn't you have a vial?

01:29:40.339 --> 01:29:42.273
Are you having trouble sleeping?

